"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-charlotte-dujardin-paris-olympics-2024-team-gb-dressage-video-b1172430.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Team GB'sCharlotte Dujardinhas pulled out of the upcomingParis Olympicsdue to \\\"an error of judgement\\\" during a coaching session, with the dressage rider provisionally banned for six months.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999940610235997, \"rank\": 5.939007070238648e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 39-year-old is Britain's joint-most decorated female Olympian, with six medals to her name, and would have gone pastLaura Kennyand held the record herself had she picked up another medal in Paris.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 455, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9997863857938651, \"rank\": 0.0002133637126527886, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.1071441991062863e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 630, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.213698463742068e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Dujardin released a statement on Tuesday to reveal she has withdrawn from the Olympics and all other competitions while an investigation takes place.\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ban remains provisional during the investigation into behaviour equestrian's governing body the FEI described as \\\"contrary to the principles of horse welfare.\\\"\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 866, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999991100416404, \"rank\": 8.146302459558632e-07, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is said the incident took place at a private stable.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin had until 4pm BST on Tuesday to respond to the allegations, and \\\"confirmed that she is the individual\\\" in the video and \\\"acknowledged that her behaviour was inappropriate\\\", according to the FEI.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1218, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardian said: \\\"A video has emerged from four years ago which shows me making an error of judgement during a coaching session.\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Understandably, the International Federation for Equestrian Sports (FEI) is investigating and I have made the decision to withdraw from all competition - including the ParisOlympics- while this process takes place.\\\"\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin won gold in both the individual and team dressage events at London 2012 and defended her individual title with Valegro four years later.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1640, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999695319, \"rank\": 3.066688703672068e-11, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1691, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valegro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valegro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also won team silver in Rio, before taking broze in both events in Tokyo on Gio.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999021788474, \"rank\": 9.782116563992728e-08, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999974741927029, \"rank\": 2.5258001786980378e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin was due to compete in Paris on new horse Imhotep, both in the individual dressage and the team event alongside Carl Hester and Lottie Fry.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.213698463742068e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\"}, {\"begin\": 1939, \"end\": 1945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.90896666134968e-19, \"text\": \"Lottie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottie_Dod\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Becky Moody is Team GB's alternate.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1957, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"score\": 0.9991382863655034, \"rank\": 0.0008619131854442043, \"text\": \"Moody\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moody's_Investors_Service\"}, {\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999940610235997, \"rank\": 5.939007070238648e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What happened was completely out of character and does not reflect how I train my horses or coach my pupils, however there is no excuse,\\\" Dujardin said.\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Make 2026 the year of working smarter  \\\"I am deeply ashamed and should have set a better example in that moment.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sincerely sorry for my actions and devastated that I have let everyone down, including Team GB, fans and sponsors.\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999940610235997, \"rank\": 5.939007070238648e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will cooperate fully with the FEI, British Equestrian Federation and British Dressage during their investigations, and will not be commenting further until the process is complete.\\\"\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2614, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2619, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Equestrian Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Equestrian_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2653, \"end\": 2669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Dressage\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Dressage\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FEI President Ingmar De Vos said: \\\"Charlotte has expressed genuine remorse for her actions, and we recognise and appreciate her willingness to take responsibility.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2767, \"end\": 2770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_De_Vos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ingmar De Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_De_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_De_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\", \"score\": 0.7487180265652532, \"rank\": 0.24453125805251255, \"text\": \"Charlotte\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Motor_Speedway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Despite the unfortunate timing, we believe this action reaffirms the FEI's commitment to welfare as the guardians of our equine partners and the integrity of our sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0186192914209311e-35, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say..